[3] Malaysia
Date: Wed 6 Jun 2007
Source: People's Daily online, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200706/06/eng20070606_381392.html>

A total of 994 dengue cases were reported in Malaysia last week [28
May-3 Jun 2007], Health Ministry Disease Control Director, Datuk Dr
Hassan Abdul Rahman, has said. [On Wed 6 Jun 2007, the national news
agency Bernama quoted Dr Rahman as saying there are 20 areas
inspected nationwide.]
From 22 May to 2 June [2007], Selangor reported 338 dengue cases.
Kuala Lumpur was 2nd on the list, with 127 cases, while Kelantan
[reported] 80. Johor, Kedah, Perak, Negeri Sembilan, and Sarawak
reported more dengue cases compared to the previous period.
"Dengue cases in Kuala Lumpur dropped from 145 to 127. Pahang,
Melaka, Sabah, and Terengganu also showed decreases," Dr Hassan said.
The Health Ministry has ordered all states and districts to activate
their operations rooms, he said.
--
